4.11	George_Dalgarno	George Dalgarno	Dalgarno was also interested in constructing what he called a 'philosophical language', now more usually referred to as universal language. A modern translation of his Ars signorum (Art of Signs, 1661) was published in 2001 in an edition that also includes his autobiography and other manuscript writings.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/92/Dalgarno_Ars_Signorum.jpg/220px-Dalgarno_Ars_Signorum.jpg
